{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/first-glance-of-openwrt","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"70d36802-c6b9-5f00-a072-db342d9a8986","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2f7ca4a531323fe8df2c04ed2ac2c672/4b190/tl-mr13u.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/2f7ca4a531323fe8df2c04ed2ac2c672/8ac56/tl-mr13u.webp 240w,\n/static/2f7ca4a531323fe8df2c04ed2ac2c672/d3be9/tl-mr13u.webp 480w,\n/static/2f7ca4a531323fe8df2c04ed2ac2c672/d00b9/tl-mr13u.webp 800w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/2f7ca4a531323fe8df2c04ed2ac2c672/09b79/tl-mr13u.jpg 240w,\n/static/2f7ca4a531323fe8df2c04ed2ac2c672/7cc5e/tl-mr13u.jpg 480w,\n/static/2f7ca4a531323fe8df2c04ed2ac2c672/4b190/tl-mr13u.jpg 800w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/2f7ca4a531323fe8df2c04ed2ac2c672/4b190/tl-mr13u.jpg\"\n            alt=\"mr13u\"\n            title=\"mr13u\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>By chance, I learned there is a widely used router OS named <strong>OpenWRT</strong>. OpenWRT stands out as a powerful and flexible open-source firmware for routers and other embedded devices, allowing users to customize and enhance the functionality of their network devices.</p>\n<p>The <a href=\"http://wiki.openwrt.org/toh/tp-link/tl-mr13u\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">TP-Link TL-MR13U</a> is a router that gained popularity for its portability and affordability. The most important feature is it contains a battery inside it. We could put it into pocket without power to provide wifi link 802.11n.</p>\n<p>After installed OpenWRT Attitude Adjustment on the TL-MR13U, I’m happy to have the router OS replaced. It’s suitable to bring the brick in my vocation :)</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/first-glance-of-openwrt","tagSlugs":["/tag/linux-system/","/tag/open-wrt/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2014-05-13T22:55:00.000Z","description":"experience of first-time openwrt installation.","tags":["Linux System","OpenWRT"],"title":"First Glance of OpenWRT","socialImage":{"publicURL":"/static/2f7ca4a531323fe8df2c04ed2ac2c672/tl-mr13u.jpg"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/first-glance-of-openwrt"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","401334301","825871152"]}